1
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,325
This is a bus ticket to Seoul.

2
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:20,325
You want me to go back to Seoul alone?

3
00:00:20,325 --> 00:00:24,500
Decide if you want to go back to Seoul alone or with me.

4
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,225
I'll be back in a while.

5
00:00:26,225 --> 00:00:28,225
Think long and hard,

6
00:00:28,875 --> 00:00:30,500
so you won't regret it later.

7
00:00:31,675 --> 00:00:34,425
If you're going to accept me as I am,

8
00:00:34,425 --> 00:00:36,775
stay here and wait for me.

9
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:40,650
If you don't have the heart to,

10
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:44,000
take the bus to Seoul alone.

11
00:00:47,825 --> 00:00:49,575
And just in case,

12
00:00:51,050 --> 00:00:53,050
let's say goodbye here.

13
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:56,650
Hurry.

14
00:01:03,325 --> 00:01:05,575
You made me laugh.

15
00:01:05,575 --> 00:01:07,575
Thanks.

16
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:12,150
Even if this is the end, I'm okay with it

17
00:01:13,775 --> 00:01:15,300
because I was happy.

18
00:01:51,525 --> 00:01:53,550
You!

19
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:58,000
I can't believe my ears.

20
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,175
What did you say?
A high school dropout?

21
00:02:01,175 --> 00:02:03,975
Everyone has a college degree these days,

22
00:02:03,975 --> 00:02:06,600
so why couldn't he get one?

23
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,725
And he operates an excavator? And he's poor?

24
00:02:09,725 --> 00:02:11,725
Are you out of your mind?

25
00:02:11,725 --> 00:02:14,025
How awful? Where did you find him?

26
00:02:14,025 --> 00:02:16,975
Did you get a lobotomy without telling me?

27
00:02:16,975 --> 00:02:20,350
Father, don't get upset over this.

28
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:21,925
What's wrong with you?

29
00:02:21,925 --> 00:02:24,250
You know how I broke their hearts.

30
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,675
You were a teacher, so how could you meet a high school dropout?

31
00:02:27,675 --> 00:02:30,125
He dropped out in his junior year?

32
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:34,875
I dropped out of college and people hold that against me. It's humiliating.

33
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,375
He should at least have a college degree.

34
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:37,300
I know.

35
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,900
Even I have a college degree.

36
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,850
I have an English Lit degree.

37
00:02:40,850 --> 00:02:43,175
And I have a law degree.

38
00:02:43,175 --> 00:02:45,025
And I have a commerce degree.

39
00:02:45,025 --> 00:02:46,500
Gwangbak, I'm very disappointed in you.

40
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,625
This is nuts.

41
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:52,175
You should be ashamed of yourself.

42
00:02:52,175 --> 00:02:55,150
I was in the Miss Korea pageant!

43
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:57,975
I can't believe how dumb you are.

44
00:02:57,970 --> 00:03:00,475
The Korean War was nothing compared to this.

45
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:01,550
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo.

46
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:03,550
We should beat some sense into you.

47
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:05,375
Dad, here.

48
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:07,075
Rude, ugly hag.

49
00:03:07,075 --> 00:03:10,325
You yelled at me to study hard, and you're seeing a high school dropout?

50
00:03:10,325 --> 00:03:11,800
Can I drop out of school?

51
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:14,500
We're wasting our time. Get out!

52
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,275
Out!

53
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,975
Go inside before I get mad.

54
00:03:46,975 --> 00:03:48,525
No, no, no.

55
00:03:48,525 --> 00:03:51,150
Why I ought to!

56
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:59,000
Are you okay?
Honey, wake up! Honey!

57
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:02,375
How can you hit him?

58
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,750
Are you a thug?

59
00:04:28,425 --> 00:04:31,475
Hey, I'm sorry I yelled at you.

60
00:04:34,275 --> 00:04:36,450
The car from before, was that yours?

61
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:38,725
It was a nice car.

62
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,100
Give me your number.

63
00:04:49,025 --> 00:04:50,875
Your phone number.

64
00:04:53,175 --> 00:04:56,900
Aeji, it's dinner time. Aeji!

65
00:05:00,075 --> 00:05:01,875
What's wrong?

66
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,675
Can't you hear me?

67
00:05:05,675 --> 00:05:08,525
Mom!

68
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:11,550
I broke the stroller.

69
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:15,150
What?

70
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,225
What do we do now?

71
00:05:18,225 --> 00:05:20,675
Your father is going to be furious.

72
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:22,750
What am I going to do?

73
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:25,500
He might kick me and Aeji out.

74
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,275
What do we do?

75
00:05:33,225 --> 00:05:34,900
Uh, father, you're home!

76
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,875
Mom! Father's home.

77
00:05:36,875 --> 00:05:40,975
You're home! You must be tired.

78
00:05:40,975 --> 00:05:42,500
What's going on? What's wrong?

79
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,000
Nothing's wrong.

80
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,975
I think you deserve this kind of welcome.

81
00:05:46,975 --> 00:05:48,325
Don't you think so, too?

82
00:05:48,325 --> 00:05:50,950
Right. Father, let's go inside.

83
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:54,675
Gwangbak's spending the night out with friends.

84
00:05:54,670 --> 00:05:56,450
She called me.

85
00:05:56,450 --> 00:06:01,675
The house felt really empty today, and I couldn't wait for you to come home.

86
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:03,275
Empty?

87
00:06:03,275 --> 00:06:05,650
Mother and Don are home.

88
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:20,875
What's wrong?
Why are you acting like this?

89
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:22,425
What do you mean?

90
00:06:22,425 --> 00:06:25,825
It's weird. Act like you normally do.

91
00:06:25,825 --> 00:06:26,650
Mother!

92
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:30,225
Uh, father, about my getting a job...

93
00:06:30,225 --> 00:06:31,800
I asked a few people.

94
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:35,775
What kind of job?
I never worked before.

95
00:06:35,775 --> 00:06:37,225
When are they getting back to you?

96
00:06:37,225 --> 00:06:39,625
They said as soon as possible.

97
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:40,800
Mother!

98
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,925
Honey, honey, wait a second. Come here.

99
00:06:43,925 --> 00:06:45,625
Why?

100
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:49,900
Tada! Pumpkin rice cake.

101
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:52,700
Your favorite, pumpkin rice cake.

102
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,650
You love pumpkin anything.

103
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:58,900
Pumpkin rice cake, pumpkin soup,

104
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:01,175
and your favorite daughter is Hobak (pumpkin).

105
00:07:01,175 --> 00:07:03,900
It's really delicious, father. Try it.

106
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,425
Later.

107
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:08,425
It won't be as good when it's cold. Try it.

108
00:07:08,425 --> 00:07:10,125
I haven't even washed my hands yet.

109
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:11,900
I'll feed it to you.

110
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,575
Isn't it delicious, father?

111
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:21,050
Oh, my! I think his hair is getting thicker.

112
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:21,950
Huh?

113
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:25,725
Oh! Right! You're getting younger.

114
00:07:25,725 --> 00:07:28,025
You look 10 years younger.

115
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,925
Did mother have some, too?

116
00:07:30,925 --> 00:07:31,800
Excuse me?

117
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,500
Of course she did.

118
00:07:35,875 --> 00:07:38,800
Father, I drew a bath for you.

119
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,175
This early?

120
00:07:41,175 --> 00:07:44,850
Our bathroom is cold,
so it's better to do it early.

121
00:07:44,850 --> 00:07:51,275
You worked hard all day,
so you should soak yourself in hot water.

122
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:55,675
Why are you rushing me tonight?

123
00:07:55,675 --> 00:07:57,150
Let me say hi to mother first.

124
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,875
The bath is getting cold. Say hi later.

125
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:02,550
Oh, man...

126
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,175
What is it?

127
00:08:11,175 --> 00:08:12,825
I need clean underwear.

128
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:15,725
I'll bring it to you. Get into the bath.

129
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,900
We've bought some time.

130
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:24,575
What if grandmother doesn't come back?

131
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,100
Is that him?

132
00:08:30,275 --> 00:08:31,625
Name?

133
00:08:33,325 --> 00:08:36,400
It's Ko Minjung.

134
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,675
This is crazy.

135
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:43,775
I looked for them everywhere.

136
00:08:43,775 --> 00:08:48,375
What are we going to do, then?

137
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:50,925
What else can we do, mom?
Let's confess.

138
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,550
Let's confess and ask for forgiveness.

139
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:56,350
He's going to blow up.

140
00:08:57,325 --> 00:09:00,250
Oh, what the heck! He can't kill us.

141
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:09,050
Oh, that was nice.

142
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:11,325
Hey, is there anything to drink?

143
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:17,300
What's wrong?

144
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:21,550
Tell me. What did you do?

145
00:09:23,075 --> 00:09:26,250
Grandmother ran away with uncle.

146
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,350
What?

147
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,700
Grandmother!

148
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,950
Uncle!

149
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,250
- Grandmother!
- Mother!

150
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,850
Grandmother!

151
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:43,300
Have you seen my mother?

152
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,475
No, I haven't.

153
00:09:54,675 --> 00:09:56,925
Mom, I'm hungry.

154
00:09:56,925 --> 00:09:59,100
I'm hungrier now that I've left home.

155
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,100
That's normal.

156
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,775
No home, no comfort.

157
00:10:03,775 --> 00:10:07,450
Can't we get something and put it on Bong's tab?

158
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,450
Don't ruin your brother's reputation.

159
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:12,450
Everyone knows he's a vice principal.

160
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:15,325
Do you have any money?

161
00:10:15,325 --> 00:10:16,975
Of course not.

162
00:10:16,975 --> 00:10:20,550
Mom, why did you name me Don?

163
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:22,200
I have no idea.

164
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,525
Your father named you before he died.

165
00:10:25,525 --> 00:10:28,475
He probably wanted you to become rich.

166
00:10:28,475 --> 00:10:30,600
Hey, look in your pocket.

167
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:34,000
Do you think I can become rich someday?

168
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,950
I have some!

169
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:36,175
You do?

170
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:38,425
Oh, you little!

171
00:10:38,425 --> 00:10:40,075
Try carrying some money next time.

172
00:10:40,075 --> 00:10:41,500
But I don't have any to carry around.

173
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,475
How about you, mom?

174
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:45,075
I was furious so I didn't bring anything.

175
00:10:45,075 --> 00:10:46,600
Hey, follow me.

176
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,350
Try to look as sad as possible.

177
00:10:55,825 --> 00:10:58,425
You used to look much sadder than that!

178
00:10:58,425 --> 00:11:01,075
Remember what you do best?

179
00:11:02,350 --> 00:11:04,700
Yes! that's it!

180
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:06,975
Follow me.

181
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,025
Oh, how cold.

182
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:18,250
Excuse me, it's nice to meet you.

183
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,250
It's nice to meet you.

184
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,100
Not really.

185
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:27,300
I fled from North Korea during the Korean War.

186
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,150
Excuse me?

187
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:32,300
And I'm starving. Can you give me some food?

188
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,625
You came from North Korea?

189
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:35,050
Yes.

190
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:39,900
He's not my son but grandson, but he hasn't eaten for days.

191
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:45,075
Please give us some food.

192
00:11:45,075 --> 00:11:47,625
She's my grandmother.

193
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:54,400
You can have these.

194
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:58,550
Thank you, thank you. God bless you.

195
00:12:03,775 --> 00:12:06,975
Hey, slow down. You'll get sick.

196
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,100
This is the last bus to Seoul!

197
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,375
If you're going to Seoul, please hurry!

198
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:43,975
This is the last bus to Seoul!

199
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:46,375
Excuse me, is this the last bus?

200
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,325
Yes.

201
00:12:47,825 --> 00:12:50,000
This is the last bus to Seoul!

202
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,775
Is anyone going to Seoul?

203
00:12:52,275 --> 00:12:54,375
The bus is leaving!

204
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:57,875
Wait for me.

205
00:13:49,225 --> 00:13:52,700
Huh? That's it? It should be bigger.

206
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:53,975
Read it.

207
00:13:54,975 --> 00:13:57,550
Choi Sangnam!

208
00:13:59,375 --> 00:14:01,350
I wrote "Wang Gwangbak,"

209
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:04,350
and I read it " My Love."

210
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:10,350
Excuse me, sir!

211
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:12,100
Please let me get off!

212
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,875
Excuse me, is there any other bus?

213
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:14,550
There's no more buses tonight.

214
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,675
The last one left just now.

215
00:15:29,214 --> 00:15:30,215
[Seoul]

216
00:15:32,850 --> 00:15:34,750
I have lots of ointment.

217
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:36,025
So leave it to me.

218
00:15:36,025 --> 00:15:38,250
I'll make it all better.

219
00:15:40,175 --> 00:15:43,050
I'll help you forget all your pain.

220
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,775
I'll be better to you.

221
00:15:44,775 --> 00:15:47,825
I won't play games and I'll do what you say.

222
00:15:47,825 --> 00:15:50,525
I'll go and come as you say.

223
00:16:13,575 --> 00:16:15,300
What a fool...

224
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:17,525
You fool!

225
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:01,650
Hello.

226
00:17:01,650 --> 00:17:03,975
- I want to report a missing person.
- Oh.

227
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:05,175
It's right over there.

228
00:17:05,175 --> 00:17:06,500
Okay.

229
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,525
It wasn't me.

230
00:17:08,525 --> 00:17:10,000
It must be a misunderstanding.

231
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,875
Circumstantial evidence says you're the one.

232
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:17,875
Minjung.

233
00:17:20,025 --> 00:17:21,850
Father,

234
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:23,424
how did you know?

235
00:17:23,424 --> 00:17:24,675
Know what?

236
00:17:24,675 --> 00:17:26,500
I didn't come here for you.

237
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,629
Why are you here?

238
00:17:30,725 --> 00:17:32,066
There's been a misunderstanding.

239
00:17:33,175 --> 00:17:35,925
Your son in law is a thief.

240
00:17:35,925 --> 00:17:37,000
Excuse me?

241
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,300
How could you steal from me?

242
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,742
I said I'd forgive you if you return them,

243
00:17:41,742 --> 00:17:43,742
but you keep insisting it wasn't you.

244
00:17:44,825 --> 00:17:46,113
What's going on here?

245
00:17:46,113 --> 00:17:50,050
Your son in law went into her house while delivering a package today.

246
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:53,075
After that, money and jewelry went missing.

247
00:17:53,070 --> 00:17:54,750
It wasn't me.

248
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,700
I came right out after pouring the rice out.

249
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:00,400
You were standing by me the whole time.

250
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,900
I really had nothing to do with that.

251
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:06,325
But I had no other visitors besides you!

252
00:18:06,325 --> 00:18:13,400
People are really sneaky these days, so you could've taken them when my eyes were closed!

253
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:17,500
Pickpockets can steal at a blink of an eye!

254
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,625
Can I talk to you?

255
00:18:28,675 --> 00:18:30,100
Minjung,

256
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:32,525
be honest with me.

257
00:18:32,525 --> 00:18:33,926
You really had nothing to do with it?

258
00:18:36,175 --> 00:18:37,425
Excuse me?

259
00:18:37,425 --> 00:18:43,201
Please make mistakes out of desperation.

260
00:18:47,425 --> 00:18:48,950
Father,

261
00:18:50,850 --> 00:18:52,710
I'd rather go to prison.

262
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:56,914
Even if the world thought I was guilty,

263
00:18:56,914 --> 00:18:59,525
I didn't think you would...

264
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:10,725
Even if the whole world casted stones at me,

265
00:19:10,725 --> 00:19:15,750
I thought you would believe me.

266
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,125
Hello. This is my business card.

267
00:19:29,546 --> 00:19:30,375
[Mun Jin Middle School
Vice Principal Wang Bong]

268
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:32,175
Yes.

269
00:19:32,175 --> 00:19:38,100
I swear on my teaching job,
my son in law didn't do it.

270
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:42,191
But the circumstances are suspicious.

271
00:19:42,675 --> 00:19:45,595
Then let's go to her house and check.

272
00:19:45,595 --> 00:19:48,375
Let's search the whole house.

273
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:50,700
I swear to god.

274
00:19:51,325 --> 00:19:52,635
I'll eat my hat.

275
00:20:14,725 --> 00:20:16,850
What did you say it looks like?

276
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:20,595
It's a pouch I always wear here.

277
00:20:20,595 --> 00:20:22,625
It's red pouch.

278
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:27,675
