It's better to be an only child?

553
00:36:36,025 --> 00:36:38,850
They say it's better to have no children.

554
00:36:38,850 --> 00:36:40,675
It's the same thing.

555
00:36:40,675 --> 00:36:43,900
Having lots of siblings is a huge headache,

556
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:47,582
unless they are loaded and giving.

557
00:36:48,325 --> 00:36:50,250
You have me, so don't worry.

558
00:36:50,250 --> 00:36:52,353
I'll make sure nobody touches you.

559
00:36:52,825 --> 00:36:56,057
Take care of your in laws.

560
00:36:56,057 --> 00:37:00,000
If anything like this happens again, you know, right?

561
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:03,625
I must return the car key and credit card.

562
00:37:03,625 --> 00:37:05,500
This is my treat.

563
00:37:05,500 --> 00:37:10,800
This is what every Korean loves, and it's called pork belly.

564
00:37:14,025 --> 00:37:15,950
It really hurt, didn't it?

565
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:18,650
I can't believe you saw sparks.

566
00:37:18,650 --> 00:37:20,025
I know the feeling.

567
00:37:20,025 --> 00:37:22,450
Which cheek was it? This one?

568
00:37:22,450 --> 00:37:23,375
This one.

569
00:37:23,375 --> 00:37:24,725
This one?

570
00:37:34,775 --> 00:37:36,325
Let's go somewhere else.

571
00:37:36,325 --> 00:37:37,675
Why?

572
00:37:46,625 --> 00:37:47,750
Oh, my!

573
00:38:40,150 --> 00:38:42,125
I'm glad I ran into you.

574
00:38:42,125 --> 00:38:44,575
Your kids are jumping like mad.

575
00:38:44,570 --> 00:38:48,699
I rang the door many times, but it didn't work.

576
00:38:48,699 --> 00:38:50,675
That can't be.

577
00:38:50,675 --> 00:38:52,135
My kids don't jump.

578
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:55,225
My ceilings about to collapse.

579
00:38:55,225 --> 00:38:57,000
Is this your first apartment?

580
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,310
Apartment noise leads to murders these days!

581
00:39:02,275 --> 00:39:04,275
I'm sorry.

582
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:06,825
I knew this would happen.

583
00:39:06,825 --> 00:39:09,118
What are you teaching those boys?

584
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:17,375
You!

585
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:19,125
You little rascals! Come here!

586
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:21,425
I told you to play quietly! Didn't I?

587
00:39:21,425 --> 00:39:23,225
Why won't you listen to me? Why?

588
00:39:23,225 --> 00:39:26,000
Do you want me to die from stress?

589
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:29,138
No! I don't want you to die!

590
00:39:29,138 --> 00:39:31,025
Go ahead! Hit me!

591
00:39:31,025 --> 00:39:33,609
It's not my kid you're killing!

592
00:39:33,925 --> 00:39:34,700
What?

593
00:39:34,700 --> 00:39:36,950
What did you say? Come here!

594
00:39:36,950 --> 00:39:40,075
How dare you say such a thing!

595
00:40:01,925 --> 00:40:03,025
Who is it?

596
00:40:03,025 --> 00:40:04,225
It's me.

597
00:40:05,225 --> 00:40:08,000
Father, how come you didn't call?

598
00:40:09,850 --> 00:40:12,675
Maybe I should've called you first.

599
00:40:12,675 --> 00:40:15,650
It's okay. Come in, father.

600
00:40:19,525 --> 00:40:21,025
I bought some snacks for the boys.

601
00:40:21,025 --> 00:40:24,250
You didn't have to.

602
00:40:24,250 --> 00:40:25,600
Where are they?

603
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:27,425
I put them to bed.

604
00:40:29,325 --> 00:40:31,264
Were you crying? What happened?

605
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:33,950
I was a bit upset.

606
00:40:33,950 --> 00:40:34,675
Because of Sedal?
I was a bit upset.

607
00:40:34,675 --> 00:40:36,275
Because of Sedal?

608
00:40:36,275 --> 00:40:38,125
Because of the boys.

609
00:40:38,850 --> 00:40:44,625
When I came home, they were jumping up and down, and the downstairs lady came up.

610
00:40:44,625 --> 00:40:46,850
Boys will be boys.

611
00:40:46,850 --> 00:40:48,850
They can't help it.

612
00:41:06,170 --> 00:41:10,825
But tell them not to bother the neighbors.

613
00:41:11,625 --> 00:41:13,972
Apartment noise is a huge deal these days.

614
00:41:14,700 --> 00:41:17,142
They should put themselves in other's shoes.

615
00:41:18,375 --> 00:41:21,025
I spanked them already.

616
00:41:21,550 --> 00:41:24,000
You didn't have to do that.

617
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,217
Just talk to them.

618
00:41:28,775 --> 00:41:30,675
I'm so upset.

619
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,450
What happened?

620
00:41:33,450 --> 00:41:36,250
Hitting them broke my heart.

621
00:41:37,075 --> 00:41:39,800
I don't know why I'm like this.

622
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,800
I hated mom,

623
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,700
but I'm turning into her.

624
00:41:45,075 --> 00:41:46,737
Especially with Bangtong.

625
00:41:48,825 --> 00:41:52,109
Are you partial to one of them?

626
00:41:52,100 --> 00:41:58,975
When I'm upset, I feel like I'm doing the right thing by punishing them,

627
00:41:58,975 --> 00:42:01,785
but when I calm down and think about it,

628
00:42:01,785 --> 00:42:05,088
I think I hit Bangtong more than Sintong.

629
00:42:07,425 --> 00:42:11,125
I swore to myself that I'd love them equally,

630
00:42:11,125 --> 00:42:14,150
but I'm doing the same thing mom did.

631
00:42:14,775 --> 00:42:17,167
And it's driving me crazy.

632
00:42:17,750 --> 00:42:19,675
That's how things are.

633
00:42:20,300 --> 00:42:26,843
The victims of domestic violence grow up and become violent.

634
00:42:27,825 --> 00:42:31,047
Don't beat your kids out of anger.

635
00:42:32,325 --> 00:42:35,825
I tell the teachers at every meeting

636
00:42:35,825 --> 00:42:39,075
not to hit the students out of anger.

637
00:42:39,075 --> 00:42:41,557
That leaves emotional scars.

638
00:42:43,475 --> 00:42:44,700
I know.

639
00:42:45,375 --> 00:42:47,500
I'll be more careful, father.

640
00:42:47,500 --> 00:42:48,675
Good.

641
00:42:51,350 --> 00:42:55,370
Is everything okay with you?

642
00:42:56,675 --> 00:42:57,606
Yes.

643
00:42:59,175 --> 00:43:01,125
I heard you're going to the gym.

644
00:43:01,125 --> 00:43:03,125
Namhyeong told me.

645
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:04,900
Yes, I thought I should exercise.

646
00:43:04,900 --> 00:43:06,900
I keep gaining weight.

647
00:43:07,450 --> 00:43:10,600
Gain weight? You?
You're so skinny.

648
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:12,900
I think you lost more weight.

649
00:43:12,900 --> 00:43:15,800
I look skinny, but I'm not.

650
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:18,325
You know I'm different from what you see.

651
00:43:20,475 --> 00:43:22,700
I think your mom's softened up a bit.

652
00:43:22,700 --> 00:43:25,900
She speaks harshly, but she's softened up.

653
00:43:26,625 --> 00:43:30,137
You should drop by and talk to her.

654
00:43:31,325 --> 00:43:32,350
I will, father.

655
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,950
I better get going.

656
00:43:37,500 --> 00:43:39,975
Hobak, can I ask you for a favor?

657
00:43:39,975 --> 00:43:42,000
Anything, except to borrow money, father.

658
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:45,925
It's Subak.

659
00:43:46,475 --> 00:43:49,925
Can you find a job for her?

660
00:43:49,925 --> 00:43:53,500
She needs to lend a hand.

661
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:55,550
I'll see what I can find, father.

662
00:43:55,550 --> 00:43:57,550
I hope I'm not putting pressure on you.

663
00:44:02,750 --> 00:44:05,525
Where's Sedal? Is he always this late?

664
00:44:05,525 --> 00:44:07,406
I think he has a lot of work.

665
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:12,700
Everything is okay, right?

666
00:44:12,700 --> 00:44:15,075
It is, father. Why do you ask?

667
00:44:15,075 --> 00:44:17,600
It's nothing. I'm glad everything's okay.

668
00:44:19,025 --> 00:44:20,675
You play golf now?

669
00:44:21,300 --> 00:44:24,225
My son is successful.

670
00:44:24,225 --> 00:44:26,191
I envy you.

671
00:44:26,500 --> 00:44:29,025
It's nothing, really.

672
00:44:29,025 --> 00:44:33,400
I need to know how to do certain things to be with the boss.

673
00:44:35,475 --> 00:44:36,875
Like this.

674
00:44:36,875 --> 00:44:41,500
This is how you stand.

675
00:44:42,970 --> 00:44:45,725
Good shot!

676
00:44:45,725 --> 00:44:49,950
Oh, I wish I could play golf.

677
00:44:49,950 --> 00:44:56,854
Everyone who's well off in this town carry around their golf bags and practice their swings and play golf.

678
00:44:56,850 --> 00:44:58,623
Your time will come.

679
00:45:01,450 --> 00:45:03,400
Did you ask your director?

680
00:45:04,050 --> 00:45:04,962
Not yet.

681
00:45:05,450 --> 00:45:07,075
You said your director is rich.

682
00:45:07,070 --> 00:45:08,325
Just ask, Sedal.

683
00:45:08,325 --> 00:45:09,925
Mom's trying to make a living.

684
00:45:09,925 --> 00:45:13,103
I'm waiting for the right timing.

685
00:45:14,025 --> 00:45:17,150
Why do you keep sleeping over here?

686
00:45:17,150 --> 00:45:19,150
What did you fight about?

687
00:45:19,150 --> 00:45:21,150
Just pretend you didn't...

688
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:27,350
Yes, director.

689
00:45:28,475 --> 00:45:29,800
Right now?

690
00:45:35,975 --> 00:45:37,450
What's going on?

691
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:43,599
What is it?

692
00:45:49,175 --> 00:45:51,050
I'm so, so lonely.

693
00:45:52,150 --> 00:45:54,125
I'm scared to be alone.

694
00:45:59,075 --> 00:46:01,400
Stay with me tonight.

695
00:46:01,700 --> 00:46:04,275
And don't go anywhere, okay?

696
00:46:08,700 --> 00:46:10,400
Let's go out for lunch.

697
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:11,675
Okay. What about Sangnam?

698
00:46:11,675 --> 00:46:14,200
He left because he has plans.

699
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:16,650
He seems to be very busy these days.

700
00:46:16,650 --> 00:46:17,775
Is something up with him?

701
00:46:17,775 --> 00:46:20,975
Who knows?
Maybe he's seeing someone.

702
00:46:28,125 --> 00:46:30,375
Go sit down. I'll bring it over.

703
00:46:38,750 --> 00:46:39,875
Did you bring it?

704
00:46:42,600 --> 00:46:43,875
Tada!

705
00:46:44,425 --> 00:46:46,675
My third grade winter vacation journal.

706
00:46:46,675 --> 00:46:49,150
Oh! Mine's from third grade, too.

707
00:46:53,050 --> 00:46:55,125
Let's write a report on them after reading.

708
00:46:55,675 --> 00:46:57,175
And your photo album?

709
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:01,150
I don't show this to just anyone.

710
00:47:01,150 --> 00:47:02,325
Tada!

711
00:47:05,900 --> 00:47:08,325
How adorable!

712
00:47:08,900 --> 00:47:12,375
Not adorable. Handsome.

713
00:47:12,375 --> 00:47:14,587
A baby less than a year old isn't "handsome."

714
00:47:14,580 --> 00:47:17,925
Look. I already look like a player.

715
00:47:17,925 --> 00:47:19,200
I was born with it.

716
00:47:21,275 --> 00:47:22,628
Not this one.

717
00:47:23,525 --> 00:47:25,150
Why not?

718
00:47:26,300 --> 00:47:27,875
It's too sexy.

719
00:47:27,875 --> 00:47:29,650
My pants are missing.

720
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:34,125
I want to see. Please show me.

721
00:47:34,575 --> 00:47:36,100
I can't...

722
00:47:39,500 --> 00:47:40,800
Oh, my!

723
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:44,950
How adorable!

724
00:47:44,950 --> 00:47:46,500
I'm embarrassed.

725
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:52,600
Give me 10 cents for every kiss.

726
00:47:57,125 --> 00:47:59,800
Advance payment. I have nine left.

727
00:48:00,475 --> 00:48:01,750
Album.

728
00:48:01,750 --> 00:48:04,400
I couldn't bring them all.

729
00:48:04,400 --> 00:48:06,000
I'll show you when you come to my house.

730
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:08,975
Is it because you had work done?

731
00:48:08,975 --> 00:48:10,475
Is that why you can't show me?

732
00:48:10,470 --> 00:48:13,050
No. I'm a natural beauty.

733
00:48:13,050 --> 00:48:15,800
I had the same face since I was a girl.

734
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:17,675
With big eyes.

735
00:48:18,175 --> 00:48:19,850
It must be nice to have many pictures.

736
00:48:20,650 --> 00:48:21,875
I don't have that many.

737
00:48:21,870 --> 00:48:23,275
This is it.

738
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:24,855
The rest of the pages are empty.

739
00:48:27,375 --> 00:48:32,000
We will become a family and fill them up.

740
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:33,425
Let's do that.

741
00:48:40,450 --> 00:48:41,438
Well...

742
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:43,875
Remember?

743
00:48:43,875 --> 00:48:45,525
My mom?

744
00:48:47,320 --> 00:48:49,325
Like you said, I'm going to forgive her.

745
00:48:50,450 --> 00:48:52,150
I won't be able to love anyone

746
00:48:53,150 --> 00:48:55,051
unless I do that first.

747
00:48:56,850 --> 00:48:59,550
You're such a good boy.

748
00:49:02,325 --> 00:49:03,875
When is the best time?

749
00:49:03,875 --> 00:49:05,350
As soon as possible.

750
00:49:05,350 --> 00:49:08,050
I told you. I don't like wasting time.

751
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:11,725
I can't sleep because I want to marry you.

752
00:49:15,300 --> 00:49:19,775
Can we not tell my family about your school?

753
00:49:19,775 --> 00:49:23,225
It has nothing to do with how I feel.

754
00:49:23,225 --> 00:49:25,150
I don't care about that stuff.

755
00:49:25,150 --> 00:49:26,275
I know.

756
00:49:26,275 --> 00:49:29,975
You don't want them to be biased.

757
00:49:29,975 --> 00:49:32,500
Right. That's it.

758
00:49:32,500 --> 00:49:35,000
Time will solve it,

759
00:49:35,000 --> 00:49:38,000
so let's not bring it up just yet.

760
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,175
Okay.

761
00:49:40,150 --> 00:49:42,100
We'll tell them later.

762
00:49:42,100 --> 00:49:43,975
I won't bring it up.

763
00:49:43,975 --> 00:49:46,350
You need to meet someone today.

764
00:49:47,225 --> 00:49:48,750
Who is it?

765
00:49:57,350 --> 00:50:00,050
This reminds me of the soup you made me.

766
00:50:01,525 --> 00:50:05,725
You made this soup on my birthday.

767
00:50:11,500 --> 00:50:13,025
You didn't know?

768
00:50:13,950 --> 00:50:16,725
You didn't have seaweed soup this morning?

769
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:19,800
Minjung!

770
00:50:40,375 --> 00:50:41,925
Minjung!

771
00:50:46,900 --> 00:50:47,875
Don't get off.

772
00:50:47,875 --> 00:50:49,025
Here.

773
00:50:49,025 --> 00:50:50,475
I made some dumplings.

774
00:50:50,475 --> 00:50:51,950
You called me for this?

775
00:50:51,950 --> 00:50:52,725
Yes.

776
00:50:52,725 --> 00:50:54,400
You like dumplings.

777
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:56,200
Eat it while you drive.

778
00:50:56,200 --> 00:50:58,025
I also packed some warm coffee.

779
00:50:58,025 --> 00:50:59,875
Go. I'll see you later.

780
00:51:14,750 --> 00:51:15,850
Sunjeong.

781
00:51:15,850 --> 00:51:18,225
You're busy. You should go.

782
00:51:20,575 --> 00:51:21,850
Thanks.

783
00:51:21,850 --> 00:51:25,350
But don't do this again.

784
00:51:25,925 --> 00:51:27,775
All people are the same.

785
00:51:28,825 --> 00:51:32,000
I'm not just some guy you used to know.

786
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:34,625
We almost got married,

787
00:51:34,625 --> 00:51:37,925
and no man would approve of that.

788
00:51:37,925 --> 00:51:39,800
Minjung,

789
00:51:39,800 --> 00:51:43,350
when we're together, don't talk about others.

790
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:44,900
It's okay.

791
00:51:44,900 --> 00:51:46,883
I'm doing this because I can.

792
00:51:46,883 --> 00:51:48,375
So don't worry.

793
00:51:51,325 --> 00:51:53,150
Why are you looking at me like that?

794
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:55,275
Are you worried about me seducing you?

795
00:51:56,525 --> 00:51:58,450
You're not capable of that.

796
00:51:58,450 --> 00:51:59,875
Huh?

797
00:51:59,875 --> 00:52:01,825
I'm not the same girl you used to know.

798
00:52:01,825 --> 00:52:04,000
It's been over 10 years.

799
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:07,875
How did you know I like dumplings?

800
00:52:07,875 --> 00:52:09,605
Even my own wife doesn't know that.

801
00:52:11,850 --> 00:52:15,125
This may sound presumptuous,

802
00:52:15,125 --> 00:52:18,450
but I think I understand your wife.

803
00:52:19,482 --> 00:52:24,700
When you lose all your money like that, women can't help it.

804
00:52:24,700 --> 00:52:26,700
She must feel very lost.

805
00:52:26,700 --> 00:52:29,700
She has to take care of you and the kids.

806
00:52:30,875 --> 00:52:34,125
It's natural to forget things like birthdays.

807
00:52:36,175 --> 00:52:37,099
I know.

808
00:52:38,075 --> 00:52:40,375
You should be nice to her.

809
00:52:40,375 --> 00:52:43,600
And you should try to rely on me a bit.

810
00:52:43,600 --> 00:52:45,525
I can't be of big help,

811
00:52:45,525 --> 00:52:47,625
but I can be there for you.

812
00:52:55,875 --> 00:52:56,951
Aunt.

813
00:53:05,675 --> 00:53:07,475
I'm right on time, right?

814
00:53:07,475 --> 00:53:09,296
Say hi. This is my aunt.

815
00:53:09,850 --> 00:53:12,600
Hello. I'm Wang Gwangbak.

816
00:53:12,600 --> 00:53:14,675
It's nice to meet you.

817
00:53:14,675 --> 00:53:18,150
I was wondering about the lucky girl.

818
00:53:18,150 --> 00:53:19,125
Isn't she perfect?

819
00:53:19,125 --> 00:53:20,274
Sit down, aunt.

820
00:53:29,375 --> 00:53:31,425
You look like a good person.

821
00:53:31,425 --> 00:53:34,225
People with big eyes are all kind hearted.

822
00:53:34,225 --> 00:53:35,200
Right?

823
00:53:35,200 --> 00:53:37,900
But he teases me, saying I look like a puppy.

824
00:53:37,900 --> 00:53:40,475
You should hear her barking.

825
00:53:43,275 --> 00:53:45,600
Sangnam told me a lot about you.

826
00:53:46,600 --> 00:53:47,975
He made fun of me?

827
00:53:47,975 --> 00:53:50,525
No, he said you're a very nice person.

828
00:53:50,525 --> 00:53:52,300
You're like his mom.

829
00:53:52,300 --> 00:53:54,300
How fake!

830
00:53:54,300 --> 00:53:57,200
Be yourself. You'll be attacking each other soon.

831
00:53:57,200 --> 00:53:59,425
We have to reveal one thing at a time.

832
00:53:59,420 --> 00:54:02,700
You're not supposed to show everything at once.

833
00:54:05,175 --> 00:54:07,050
I need to get this.

834
00:54:07,050 --> 00:54:08,425
I'll be right back.

835
00:54:09,500 --> 00:54:10,675
Yes.

836
00:54:16,725 --> 00:54:18,597
I'm not looking for anything else.

837
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:21,825
I just want you to be happy with Sangnam.

838
00:54:21,825 --> 00:54:22,901
That's all.

839
00:54:23,925 --> 00:54:25,700
I won't forget it.

840
00:54:27,525 --> 00:54:31,175
You're the first woman he wants to marry.

841
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:34,425
You heard about our family, right?

842
00:54:34,425 --> 00:54:35,925
Yes.

843
00:54:35,925 --> 00:54:39,350
Unfortunately, you can't move out.

844
00:54:39,350 --> 00:54:42,320
I know we have to live with his father.

845
00:54:43,375 --> 00:54:46,400
But the house is big, so it should be fine.

846
00:54:46,400 --> 00:54:48,325
You can have the second floor.

847
00:54:49,425 --> 00:54:50,550
The second floor?

848
00:54:50,550 --> 00:54:52,900
And there isn't much to buy.

849
00:54:52,900 --> 00:54:54,900
Maybe a new bed.

850
00:54:54,900 --> 00:54:58,100
We bought new furniture recently.

851
00:54:58,875 --> 00:54:59,725
Okay.

852
00:54:59,725 --> 00:55:02,225
And the house isn't very old.

853
00:55:02,850 --> 00:55:04,850
It looked pretty old.

854
00:55:04,850 --> 00:55:08,250
I ran into him by his house one time.

855
00:55:08,250 --> 00:55:10,275
That can't be.

856
00:55:10,275 --> 00:55:12,550
It's only 3 years old.

857
00:55:13,200 --> 00:55:14,700
Really?

858
00:55:14,700 --> 00:55:18,300
There are many people there, so no wonder.

859
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:21,025
And there won't be much work.

860
00:55:21,025 --> 00:55:22,800
The garden is big,

861
00:55:22,800 --> 00:55:25,125
but we have someone who takes care of it.

862
00:55:25,125 --> 00:55:26,500
So you won't have to worry about that.

863
00:55:26,500 --> 00:55:28,500
I'm sorry,

864
00:55:28,500 --> 00:55:31,000
but I don't understand what you're saying.

865
00:55:32,125 --> 00:55:33,925
I'm talking about the house you'll live in.

866
00:55:33,925 --> 00:55:35,275
I know,

867
00:55:35,275 --> 00:55:38,575
but having the second floor or garden sounds

868
00:55:38,575 --> 00:55:41,650
weird when he lives in the basement.

869
00:55:41,650 --> 00:55:43,525
He lives in the basement?

870
00:55:43,520 --> 00:55:45,000
Did Sangnam tell you that?

871
00:55:48,975 --> 00:55:52,350
You should yell at him. He tricked you.

872
00:55:52,950 --> 00:55:54,022
Excuse me?

873
00:56:05,725 --> 00:56:07,275
Are you okay?

874
00:56:14,550 --> 00:56:15,900
What is it?

875
00:56:19,750 --> 00:56:22,375
I met with my friends a few days ago.

876
00:56:22,375 --> 00:56:23,525
Yeah.

877
00:56:23,525 --> 00:56:25,775
And one of them saw

878
00:56:25,775 --> 00:56:29,650
his son in law meeting some other woman.

879
00:56:31,525 --> 00:56:34,228
And he was wondering what to do about it.

880
00:56:34,920 --> 00:56:36,950
Why would he wonder about that?

881
00:56:36,950 --> 00:56:40,850
He should have gone straight over to them,

882
00:56:40,850 --> 00:56:43,400
yell at the evil witch

883
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:46,072
and beat the crap out of her.

884
00:56:46,750 --> 00:56:47,675
That's what he should do?

885
00:56:47,675 --> 00:56:49,275
Of course!

886
00:56:49,275 --> 00:56:50,975
Why would he worry about that?

887
00:56:50,975 --> 00:56:54,425
Tell him to call her and teach her a lesson.

888
00:56:54,425 --> 00:56:55,975
He should nip it in the bud.

889
00:57:00,125 --> 00:57:02,822
It's not Minjung or Sedal, is it?

890
00:57:03,600 --> 00:57:06,759
It's not Minjung or Sedal. It's someone else.

891
00:57:21,425 --> 00:57:23,575
I miss mom.

892
00:57:24,625 --> 00:57:28,413
I'm hungry. Where's my mom?

893
00:57:29,900 --> 00:57:32,000
Does she hate me now?

894
00:57:33,950 --> 00:57:38,089
If I see her, I should say I'm sorry.

895
00:58:08,450 --> 00:58:09,700
Why did I do that?

896
00:58:09,700 --> 00:58:11,100
Because you're happy.

897
00:58:11,100 --> 00:58:13,550
Correct.

898
00:58:13,550 --> 00:58:14,700
What were you doing?

899
00:58:14,700 --> 00:58:19,025
I was meeting a little girl in third grade.

900
00:58:20,025 --> 00:58:23,300
See? You're better with words than I am.

901
00:58:23,300 --> 00:58:24,425
You're a writer.

902
00:58:25,975 --> 00:58:30,525
I was meeting a lovely ten year old boy.

903
00:58:31,340 --> 00:58:36,000
I think I know why you wanted to do this.

904
00:58:36,825 --> 00:58:40,600
Go to bed. You need your beauty sleep.

905
00:58:40,600 --> 00:58:43,000
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

906
00:58:50,175 --> 00:58:52,600
This won't do. Come out.

907
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:54,500
Right now?

908
00:58:54,500 --> 00:58:56,500
I can't do this. I miss you too much.

909
01:00:00,025 --> 01:00:01,700
I think we should stop.

910
01:00:03,800 --> 01:00:04,675
Let's go.

911
01:00:05,325 --> 01:00:06,675
I'll take you home.

912
01:00:18,075 --> 01:00:19,225
You live here?

913
01:00:21,075 --> 01:00:23,649
Go in. I'll see you tomorrow.

914
01:00:36,625 --> 01:00:38,750
Good night. I'm going.

915
01:00:50,225 --> 01:00:53,850
Waiting for Gwangbak's future husband brings me back memories.

916
01:00:54,500 --> 01:00:57,025
Of when I came to meet you.

917
01:00:57,020 --> 01:00:58,750
How was it?

918
01:00:59,400 --> 01:01:01,025
I was nervous.

919
01:01:01,025 --> 01:01:05,223
I used to hang out here all the time,
so I wasn't nervous at all.

920
01:01:05,223 --> 01:01:06,875
The first impression is the key.

921
01:01:06,870 --> 01:01:10,250
Men don't like women with lots of sisters.

922
01:01:10,250 --> 01:01:11,825
So be lady like,

923
01:01:11,825 --> 01:01:13,931
and watch what you say.

924
01:01:13,931 --> 01:01:17,050
Just be yourselves. You can't fool him.

925
01:01:17,050 --> 01:01:18,225
He should be here.

926
01:01:20,025 --> 01:01:21,650
Hey, sucker!

927
01:01:22,875 --> 01:01:25,175
You look nice! The best!

928
01:01:25,175 --> 01:01:26,443
I always look nice.

929
01:01:27,125 --> 01:01:28,250
You're full of yourself.

930
01:01:28,250 --> 01:01:29,775
Let's go in. Everyone's waiting.

931
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:32,382
Am I shaking?

932
01:01:33,900 --> 01:01:36,450
Don't forget what you promised.

933
01:01:36,450 --> 01:01:37,725
I won't.

934
01:01:39,075 --> 01:01:40,100
Let's go.

935
01:01:42,975 --> 01:01:44,100
He's here.

936
01:01:44,750 --> 01:01:45,900
He is?

937
01:01:50,925 --> 01:01:53,035
Hello. It's nice to meet you.

938
01:01:53,035 --> 01:01:54,725
I'm Choi Sangnam.

939
01:01:56,475 --> 01:01:57,750
Welcome.

940
01:01:58,125 --> 01:01:59,475
Welcome.

941
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:01,325
Here.

942
01:02:03,600 --> 01:02:07,750
I never gotten flowers from a man before!

943
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:11,850
He brought dried yellow corvina and fruit, too.

944
01:02:12,825 --> 01:02:15,050
My fridge needed restocking!

945
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:18,875
Come and sit down.

946
01:02:19,625 --> 01:02:20,675
Sit.

947
01:02:21,075 --> 01:02:22,400
Sit here.

948
01:02:37,425 --> 01:02:38,875
He's handsome.

949
01:02:38,870 --> 01:02:40,475
Huh? Yeah.

950
01:02:48,450 --> 01:03:14,000
Subtitles by KBS World

951
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:15,950
- What school did you go to?
- Excuse me?

952
01:03:15,950 --> 01:03:18,250
Did you study abroad?

953
01:03:18,250 --> 01:03:19,075
Actually...

954
01:03:19,075 --> 01:03:21,775
- You're getting a daughter in law.
- What?

955
01:03:21,775 --> 01:03:23,775
She's our daughter.

956
01:03:23,770 --> 01:03:24,925
She's pretty.

957
01:03:24,925 --> 01:03:26,000
She is?

958
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:28,525
- It's mine.
- What? I saw it first!

959
01:03:28,525 --> 01:03:31,000
I'm scared. Come quickly.

960
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:32,500
Hurry up!

961
01:03:32,500 --> 01:03:33,300
What are you doing?

962
01:03:33,300 --> 01:03:36,325
Why aren't you calling me?

963
01:03:36,325 --> 01:03:38,550
I'm sleeping with my wife.

964
01:03:38,550 --> 01:03:39,750
Are you out of your mind?

965
01:03:39,750 --> 01:03:42,025
I had high hope for you!

966
01:03:42,025 --> 01:03:43,850
How could you fall for him?

967
01:03:43,850 --> 01:03:45,850
I wish you'd trust me with this.

